>
</p></sec><sec id="Sec3"><title>Exclusion criteria</title><p>Patients fulfilling one or more of the following criteria will not be included:<list list-type="bullet"><list-item><p>A history of stroke or intracranial bleeding</p></list-item><list-item><p>A history of reversible ischaemic deficits (duration of symptoms 24&#x02013;72 hours)</p></list-item><list-item><p>A history of transient ischaemic attacks (duration of symptoms&#x02009;&#x0003c;&#x02009;24&#x000a0;hours)</p></list-item><list-item><p>Diagnosis of neurodegenerative disorders such as Alzheimer&#x02019;s, multiple sclerosis etc.</p></list-item><list-item><p>Contraindications to magnetic resonance imaging (MRI)</p></list-item></list>
</p></sec></body><back><fn-group><fn><p>The online version of the original article can be found under doi:10.1186/s13063-016-1373-6.</p></fn></fn-group><ref-list id="Bib1"><title>Reference</title><ref id="CR1"><label>1.</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Vedel</surname><given-names>A</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>Perfusion Pressure Cerebral Infarct (PPCI) trial - the importance of mean arterial pressure during cardiopulmonary bypass to prevent cerebral complications after cardiac surgery: study protocol for a randomised controlled trial</article-title><source>Trials</source><year>2016</year><volume>17</volume><fpage>247</fpage><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1186/s13063-016-1373-6</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">27189028</pub-id></element-citation></ref></ref-list></back></article>